The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Kochi, April 23 (PTI): A special court today permitted the CBI to conduct further investigation in a graft case in which CPM Kerala secretary Pinarayi Vijayan is an accused.          
	The case relates to the award of contracts to renovate three hydel projects to Canadian firm SNC-Lavalin in 1998 when Vijayan was power minister. The Kerala court also issued summons to the firm.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Delhi government has asked authorities of temples and gurdwaras, not to allow begging in and around their complexes ahead of the October Commonwealth Games. The social welfare department has identified 12 areas as zero tolerance zones and plans to increase the number of mobile squads to catch and prosecute beggars. It is using the (Bombay) Prevention of Begging Act, 1959, that authorises police to detain anyone found begging on the streets.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): A passenger from Sydney was deported from Bangalore airport when he mentioned the nature of his visit to India as secret in the immigration form. Mohammed Qadir, who had arrived via Singapore, told investigators he was in Bangalore to collect a consignment from one Robert Green but failed to answer many questions.                  
	 Ballia (PTI): Robbers killed a bank employee and a security guard on an Uttar Pradesh highway on Friday and left with about Rs 10 lakh that was being transferred from one branch to another.                  
	 Vadodara (PTI): Gujarat chief minister Narendra Modi has asked the Prime Minister to take up on the margins of the upcoming SAARC Summit the issue of the release of 584 Gujarati fishermen lodged in Pakistani jails.                  
	 Chandigarh (PTI): About 23 lakh children below the age of five are expected to be immunised against polio during a three-day programme from April 25 across 11 districts of Haryana.                                                                                                                                              
